Ikat’ika longed to find someone worthy of facing him in one-on-one combat. His opportunity came when the great Worf, son of Mogh, was brought aboard his station. Worf and Ikat’ika fought long and, though Ikat’ika had a distinct advantage, he could not finish off his Klingon opponent. Refusing to kill such an admirable challenger, Ikat’ika defied orders, choosing to give up his own life, rather than compromise his own honor.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
